COMMERCIAL / SCALABILITY TRACK
================================================================================
Items required before the game could be sold or distributed publicly.
Ordered by priority.

BLOCKING — Must fix before distribution
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DB Indexes — Add indexes on stats(game_id), stats(player_id), stats(team_id),
  and stats(team_id, game_id). Currently absent. After 10+ seasons (~270,000+
  stat rows) queries in Stats, Records, and season advance will visibly slow.
  One migration, immediate protection.

Migration Versioning — The current ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN pattern works but
  is fragile. A schema change on a 5-season save can break it with no recovery
  path. Add a schema_version key to the settings table and a numbered migration
  runner so existing saves upgrade cleanly on launch.

Multiple Save Files — The DB path (nfl-simulator.db) is hardcoded in
  database.ts. Customers expect multiple dynasties. Needs a save picker at
  launch that swaps the active DB file path before the database module loads.

Background Simulation — simulateGame runs synchronously on the Electron main
  thread. Simulating a full season or multiple seasons freezes the UI. Needs
  a worker thread or queue so sim runs in the background and the UI stays
  responsive — table stakes for a "sim to end of season" feature.

Code Signing + Auto-Update — Electron apps without code signing trigger OS
  security warnings (macOS Gatekeeper, Windows SmartScreen) that will tank
  reviews. Needs electron-builder code signing and electron-updater wired up
  before any public distribution.

Windows Build Verification — The app is developed on macOS. better-sqlite3
  is a native module that must be built per platform. Windows path separators,
  file dialogs, and native module binaries all need explicit testing. Most
  desktop gaming customers are on Windows.

IMPORTANT — Fix before growing the codebase further
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Fat IPC Handlers — Business logic is scattered across contractHandlers.ts,
  simHandlers.ts, and seasonHandlers.ts. The service layer (ContractService,
  SeasonService, TradeService) is the right pattern — more logic should move
  there so handlers are thin IPC bridges only.

JS → TS Conversion — generatePlayers.js, getStandings.js, seedTeams.js, and
  simulatePlayoffs.js are still plain JavaScript. No type safety, no IDE
  completion. Must be converted before bringing in contributors or the
  codebase becomes inconsistent.

Automated Tests — Zero test coverage. The simulation engine, CPU GM logic,
  and trade evaluator are exactly the kind of business logic that needs
  regression tests. One bad season advance bug can corrupt a long-running
  save silently.

Reduce `any` in IPC Handlers — Most handler callbacks use `any` extensively,
  effectively turning off TypeScript for the data layer. Needs typed request/
  response interfaces as the feature set grows.

FUTURE DEPTH — Required to compete with OOTP-tier games
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Sim Speed Control — Fast / slow / pause controls while simulation runs in
  background. Standard expectation in the genre.

Multi-Season Batch Simulation — "Sim 5 seasons" with a progress bar. Requires
  background simulation to be implemented first.

Realistic Schedule Generation — Current schedule is random matchups. Needs
  division-based scheduling (home/away splits, divisional games weighted).

Per-Team Franchise History — Records, retired numbers, dynasty timeline per
  team. Partial today (champions only).

Player Morale / Personality — Affects re-sign decisions, locker room culture,
  performance variance. A core OOTP mechanic.

In-Game Narrative / Play-by-Play — Text play-by-play during simulation.
  Stats-only output today limits immersion significantly.

Franchise Tag + Tender System — Standard NFL roster mechanic missing today.

League Expansion / Relocation — Add teams, move teams, custom identities.

